Actress, Adesua Wellington has revealed how God saved her from a Postpartum haemorrhage, as her son clocks one. The actress took to her Instagram page on Tuesday to celebrate her son as he clocks one. She uploaded an emotional video of the birth journey and wrote, “A year ago, God gave me the best gift ever. He placed the most precious jewel in my care. A year ago, God saved my life after suffering a postpartum haemorrhage and I’m still here only because he had his way. It’s been a year filled with lots of love, joy, peace and laughter. “Hazaiah, the one who Yahweh sees, champ, my joyful baby, my funny baby, my pacesetter after Jesus, you are the light of our lives I am so grateful to God for you. Nations will come to your light and kings to the brightness of your rising, you will forever be the head and not the tail “The Lord will shield you, announce you, defend you and favour you.” Juwon Is My Son 100%, Mercy Aigbe’s Ex- Husband Confirms Paternity Gospel Singer, Sammie Okposo, Publicly Apologises For Cheating On His Wife She added, “Anyone who curses you is cursed. I declare that you are a city set upon a hill, your glory will never be hidden. You are the salt of the earth, you will never lose your flavour; you will always be a source of joy in Jesus name, Amen. I love you more than I can possibly put in words. My sunshine. My baby. My darling. Happy birthday ZAZA. You mean the world to us.” In November 2017, the actress got married to Nigerian singer and actor, Bankole Wellington, popularly known as Banky W. The duo welcomed their son In January 2020.